<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-20T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-20T19:00:00-05:00" n="664" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d664">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2741a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Third Secretary of Embassy in
                                    Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wendelin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-20T20:00:00-04:00">August 20, 1936—8
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>90. The United Press from London today says that “the Spanish
                                Government in the last few days has issued two decrees declaring a
                                blockade of various coastal areas but no foreign Power so far has
                                recognized the blockade.”</p>
                            <p>Telegraph briefly any information that you can discreetly obtain on
                                this subject.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>